metadata.description:
Nall覺han is a rural town and district of Ankara Province in the Central Anatolia region of Turkey, 157 km from the city of Ankara.  Nall覺han is named after a caravanserai on the ancient Silk Road to the Orient next to the river Nall覺. There has been a settlement here for thousands of years.
